SIMPLE: surely
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Surely
<hw>Sure"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a
sure or certain manner; certainly; infallibly; undoubtedly;
assuredly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the day that thou eatest thereof thou shalt <qex>surely</qex>
die.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. ii. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that created something out of nothing, <qex>surely</qex> can
raise great things out of small.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without danger; firmly; steadly; securely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that walketh uprightly walketh <qex>surely</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Prov. x. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Surement</ent>⟦br⟧
